Exp 1 Lab on web services  


To develop and deploy a simple web service using Python Flask framework and access it through 
a web browser. 

Software Requirements 

• Windows 10/11/Ubuntu 
• Python 3.x 
• Flask Library 
• Web Browser (Chrome/Edge) 
A web service is a software system designed to support communication between applications 
over a network using HTTP protocol. Flask is a lightweight web framework in Python that 
allows us to create web services easily. 

Procedure 

1. Install Python software. 
2. Install Flask library using pip command. 
3. Create a Python file named webservice.py. 
4. Write Flask web service code. 
5. Run the program using command prompt. 
6. Open browser and access the URLs. 
7. Observe the output. 

Program 

